# Grammar extensions beyond upstream (sqlglot v30.12.0) — the Class-A divergence ledger.
# One JSON object per line. Each row is a construct sqlglot-go parses STRUCTURALLY that pinned
# upstream does NOT (it falls back to exp.Command or raises). See DEVIATIONS.md "Grammar
# extensions beyond upstream" and AGENTS.md "How deviations are tracked".
#
# Fields:
#   id        — stable slug
#   dialect   — "" (base) | "mysql" | "postgres" | ...
#   sql       — a canonical example
#   upstream  — pinned-upstream behavior: "command" | "parse_error"
#   go_kind   — the root Kind class name sqlglot-go parses it to
#   reconcile — what to do if the pin-tripwire fires (upstream caught up)
#
# Enforced by extension_tripwire_test.go: TestUpstreamExtensionsGoSide (we parse it -> go_kind)
# and TestUpstreamExtensionsTripwire (pinned upstream still does `upstream`; fires at bump time).
{"id":"pg-explain","dialect":"postgres","sql":"EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, FORMAT JSON) SELECT a FROM t","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Describe","reconcile":"If upstream adds structural Postgres EXPLAIN, adopt its node shape (it will likely reuse exp.Describe) and delete this row + the Postgres EXPLAIN->DESCRIBE tokenizer alias / explain parser."}
{"id":"mysql-insert-set","dialect":"mysql","sql":"INSERT INTO t SET a = 1, b = 2","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Insert","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural MySQL INSERT ... SET support, adopt upstream's node/arg shape and parser/generator behavior, decide explicitly whether the canonical Schema + one-row Values desugaring remains intentional, remove the local INSERT SET extension path, and delete this row."}
{"id":"mysql-replace","dialect":"mysql","sql":"REPLACE INTO t VALUES (1)","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Insert","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural MySQL REPLACE support, adopt upstream's node/arg shape and parser/generator behavior, remove the local REPLACE tokenizer/parser marker/generator extension path, and delete this row."}
{"id":"pg-unicode-identifier","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SELECT count(*) FROM U&\"inf\\006Frmation_schema\".tables","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Select","reconcile":"If a future pin adds Postgres U&\"...\" unicode-identifier support, adopt its decoding/node shape (decide whether decoding into a plain quoted Identifier, vs upstream's raw UnicodeString for U&'...' strings, stays intentional), and delete this row. See DEVIATIONS §1.7."}
{"id":"mysql-describe-column","dialect":"mysql","sql":"DESCRIBE t c","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Describe","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural MySQL DESCRIBE tbl [col|wild], adopt upstream's node/arg shape, remove the local column-consume in parseDescribeStructured + the generator branch, and delete this row. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"pg-set-role","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET ROLE admin","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural Postgres SET special-forms, adopt its SetItem kinds, remove the postgres SET parsers in dialect_postgres_set.go + the generator branches, and delete this row and the sibling pg-set-* rows. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"pg-set-session-authorization","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION bob","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"See pg-set-role."}
{"id":"pg-set-time-zone","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET TIME ZONE 'UTC'","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"See pg-set-role."}
{"id":"pg-set-names","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET NAMES 'utf8'","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"See pg-set-role."}
{"id":"pg-set-constraints","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET CONSTRAINTS ALL DEFERRED","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"See pg-set-role."}
{"id":"pg-set-session-characteristics","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET SESSION CHARACTERISTICS AS TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL SERIALIZABLE","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"See pg-set-role."}
{"id":"mysql-into-outfile","dialect":"mysql","sql":"SELECT * FROM t INTO OUTFILE '/tmp/x'","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Select","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural MySQL SELECT ... INTO OUTFILE, adopt upstream's Into node/arg shape (kind + export options) and remove ALL of this extension's touch points, then delete this row: parser — the OUTFILE/DUMPFILE branch in parseInto, parseIntoOutfile/parseOutfileExportOptions/parseExportValue, isOutfileKeyword/isOutfileKeywordToken, the trailing-INTO grab (+ trailing-modifier guard) in parseQueryModifiers, the file-write hoist in parseSetOperations, and validateFileWriteIntoPlacement (called from parseBatchStatements); generator — the file-write branch in intoSQL, the isFileWrite inline-render branch in selectSQL, and the trailing-into render in setOperationsSQL. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"mysql-into-dumpfile","dialect":"mysql","sql":"SELECT * FROM t INTO DUMPFILE '/tmp/x'","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Select","reconcile":"See mysql-into-outfile."}
{"id":"pg-user-type-typed-literal","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SELECT public.foo 'x'","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Select","reconcile":"If a future pin adds structural Postgres user-type space typed-literals (`<type-name> 'string'` with no AS), adopt upstream's node shape and remove this extension's touch points in parser/parser.go, then delete this row: the two pgTypedLiteralCast hooks (in parseAtom, and in parseType's keyword-name parseColumn fallback) and the helpers pgTypedLiteralCast, isPGTypeNameChain, isPGStringConstantToken, parsePGTypedLiteralValue, plus the pgReservedValueFunctionTokens set. Do NOT remove the parseAlias string-alias gate: it is now the general per-dialect Dialect.StringAliases port (parser.py:1780,8490-8492), independent of this typed-literal extension, and removing it would reintroduce implicit string aliases in base/postgres. Note the port originally mis-parsed the type-name-plus-string as a string alias because parseStringAsIdentifier was called unconditionally, vs upstream's STRING_ALIASES gate (False for base/postgres; mysql/tsql/sqlite override to True) — that is now fixed generically by Dialect.StringAliases; this extension additionally folds the type-name case into Cast(Literal, DataType(user-defined)) at the primary-expression level so it fires in every position. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"pg-start-transaction","dialect":"postgres","sql":"START TRANSACTION READ ONLY","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Transaction","reconcile":"If a future pin maps Postgres START->BEGIN (so START TRANSACTION parses structurally), adopt upstream's node shape and remove this extension's touch points, then delete this row: the START->BEGIN keyword entry in dialects/postgres.go and the tokens.ONLY match added to the parseTransaction mode loop in parser/stmt_transaction.go. Verified against PostgreSQL 17.6. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"mysql-start-transaction-snapshot","dialect":"mysql","sql":"START TRANSACTION WITH CONSISTENT SNAPSHOT","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Transaction","reconcile":"If a future pin parses MySQL START TRANSACTION WITH CONSISTENT SNAPSHOT structurally, adopt upstream's node/mode shape and remove the mysql-gated WITH CONSISTENT SNAPSHOT branch in parser/stmt_transaction.go's parseTransaction mode loop, then delete this row. Real MySQL 8.0.33 accepts this form; real PostgreSQL 17.6 rejects it, so the branch is gated to mysql. See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"release-savepoint","dialect":"postgres","sql":"RELEASE SAVEPOINT s","upstream":"parse_error","go_kind":"Savepoint","reconcile":"If a future pin adds a structural savepoint node, adopt its shape and remove this extension's touch points, then delete this row: parseSavepointStatement in parser/stmt_transaction.go, the parseStatement hook in parser/parser.go, the KindSavepoint node + savepointSQL generator, and the DEVIATIONS §1.8 entry. Note SAVEPOINT (without RELEASE) is NOT a ledgered parse_error case — upstream mis-parses it as an Alias, so it is tracked as the §1.8 correctness fix instead. Verified against PostgreSQL 17.6 and MySQL 8.0.33. See DEVIATIONS §1.8."}
{"id":"pg-set-scoped-role","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SET LOCAL ROLE admin","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"If a future pin structures Postgres SET [SESSION|LOCAL] ROLE / SESSION AUTHORIZATION, adopt its shape and remove the scoped-form handling in parser/stmt_set.go's parseSetItemAssignment (plus the SetItem `scope` arg + its generator rendering), then delete this row. Sibling of pg-set-role: the bare SET ROLE is pg-set-role; this covers the SESSION/LOCAL-scoped spelling, which pins the same SetItem kind with the scope preserved. Verified against PostgreSQL 17.6."}
{"id":"mysql-set-password","dialect":"mysql","sql":"SET PASSWORD FOR 'u'@'h' = 'x'","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Set","reconcile":"If a future pin structures MySQL SET PASSWORD [FOR user] = value, adopt its node/arg shape and remove parseSetItemPassword + parseMySQLUserSpec (parser/dialect_mysql_set_show.go), the PASSWORD entry in mysqlSetParsers, and the PASSWORD case in the setItemSQL generator, then delete this row. Note the bare SET PASSWORD = x was a plain assignment before this extension and is now folded into the same kind=PASSWORD SetItem. Verified valid syntax on MySQL 8.0.33."}
{"id":"mysql-show-create-user","dialect":"mysql","sql":"SHOW CREATE USER 'u'","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Show","reconcile":"If a future pin adds MySQL SHOW CREATE USER to its SHOW_PARSERS, adopt its shape and remove the CREATE USER entry in parser/stmt_show.go's showParsers + the CREATE USER user-spec branch in parseShowMySQL's target switch, then delete this row. Modeled like the sibling SHOW CREATE * forms (Show.this = 'CREATE USER'); the target is a MySQL user spec name[@host] via parseMySQLUserSpec. Verified valid syntax on MySQL 8.0.33."}
{"id":"pg-show-guc","dialect":"postgres","sql":"SHOW search_path","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Show","reconcile":"If a future pin structures Postgres SHOW { name | ALL | special }, adopt its node/arg shape and remove this extension's touch points, then delete this row: the `delete(cfg.Commands, tokens.SHOW)` in dialects/postgres.go, the postgres branch of parseShow -> parsePostgresShow (parser/stmt_show.go), the shared parsePostgresConfigParam + pgConfigSpecialParams + matchUnquotedTextSeq, and the postgres branch of showSQL (generator/stmt_show.go). Shares the config-param parser with pg-reset. Verified against PostgreSQL 17.6 (grammar accepts name/ALL/TIME ZONE/TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL/SESSION AUTHORIZATION; rejects trailing tokens and bare SHOW). See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
{"id":"pg-reset","dialect":"postgres","sql":"RESET search_path","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Reset","reconcile":"If a future pin structures Postgres RESET { name | ALL }, adopt its node/arg shape and remove this extension's touch points, then delete this row: the removal of the RESET->COMMAND keyword in dialects/postgres.go (restore it), parseResetStatement + the parseStatement hook (parser/parser.go), the shared parsePostgresConfigParam, the KindReset node + Reset builder, and resetSQL (generator/stmt_transaction.go). NOTE MySQL RESET stays COMMAND (RESET MASTER/REPLICA is a privileged admin op, semantically distinct) — do not touch dialects/mysql.go. Shares the config-param parser with pg-show-guc. Verified against PostgreSQL 17.6 (grammar accepts name/ALL/TIME ZONE/TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL/SESSION AUTHORIZATION; rejects trailing tokens and bare RESET). See DEVIATIONS 'Grammar extensions beyond upstream'."}
